echo "System Utilities Practice"   → Displays message on terminal.
clear                             → Clears screen.
date                              → Shows current date & time.
uptime                            → Displays system running time.
cal                               → Shows current month calendar.
pwd                               → Shows current directory.
whoami                            → Displays logged-in user.
history                           → Shows previously executed commands.

pwd                      → Check current location.
mkdir ProjectData        → Create new project folder.
cd ProjectData           → Enter the folder.
touch file.txt           → Create a file.
ls                       → List files.
mv file.txt ..           → Move file to parent directory.
cd ..                    → Go back to previous directory.
rmdir ProjectData        → Remove empty directory.

who                      → Check logged-in users.
sudo passwd alice        → Reset Alice’s password.
sudo usermod -l bob_lead bob_dev   → Rename Bob’s username.
sudo groupadd leads      → Create new group.
sudo usermod -aG leads bob_lead    → Add Bob to group.
sudo userdel -r charlie  → Delete Charlie’s account.
sudo useradd diana       → Create new user Diana.
sudo groupadd design     → Create design group.
sudo usermod -aG design diana      → Add Diana to group.
sudo chown -R bob_lead /shared/projects → Change ownership.
su                       → Switch to root user.
sudo gpasswd design      → Set group password.


ps aux                   → View all running processes.
pstree                   → Show process hierarchy.
pgrep process_name       → Find PID of process.
nice -n 10 command       → Run process with low priority.
renice 10 -p PID         → Change priority of running process.
kill PID                 → Terminate process.
pkill process_name       → Kill process by name.
killall process_name     → Kill all instances.
fg                       → Bring background process to foreground.
bg                       → Resume process in background.
xkill                    → Kill process via GUI.

free -h                  → Check memory usage.
cat /proc/meminfo        → Detailed memory info.
top                      → Real-time monitoring.
htop                     → Interactive monitoring.
vmstat                   → Check swap/memory stats.
sar -r                   → Analyze memory usage history.
ps aux --sort=-%mem      → Find highest memory usage process.



time        → Measures execution time.
tty         → Shows terminal device.
which       → Finds command path.
ping        → Tests network connectivity.
ifconfig    → Network configuration.
pr          → Formats output for printing.
lp/lpr      → Printing commands.
lpstat      → Printer status.
lpq         → Print queue.
lprm        → Remove print jobs.
cancel      → Cancel print job.
mail        → Mail utility.


fork        → Process creation (used in programming, not shell).
exec        → Replace process image.
getpid      → Get process ID.
wait        → Wait for child process.
close       → Close file descriptor.
stat        → File metadata access.
opendir     → Open directory stream.
readdir     → Read directory entries.



cp          → Copy files.
wc          → Count file content.
grep        → Search text.
tr          → Translate characters.
sort        → Sort file content.
head/tail   → View portions of file.
diff        → Compare files.
comm        → Compare sorted files.
less/more   → View file content.
file        → Identify file type.
type        → Show command type.
split       → Split files.
cmp         → Compare binary files.
tar         → Archive files.
find        → Search files.
vim         → Text editor.
gzip/bzip2  → Compression tools.
unzip       → Extract zip.
locate      → Fast file search.



login       → Login to system.
logout      → Logout session.
exit        → Exit shell.
groupdel    → Delete group.
chage       → Manage password expiry.
chgrp       → Change group ownership.
chfn        → Change user info.


df              → Disk usage.
du              → Directory size.
dmidecode       → Hardware memory info.
getconf PAGE_SIZE → Memory page size.





